Hurricane Isaac weakened to a
tropical storm about 50 miles (80) kilometers) west-southwest of
New Orleans as its top sustained winds dropped to 70 miles per
hour, the National Hurricane Center said at 3 p.m. East Coast
time.  The storm is still causing life-threatening storm surges
and inland flooding, the center said. Itâ€™s moving northwest at 6
